cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG 

The paper discusses the use of natural language processing and computer vision in interpreting visually grounded navigation instructions, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on natural language processing and understanding. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely, as the paper discusses the use of vision methods in interpreting navigation instructions. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category, as the paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning in the Matterport3D Simulator. 

cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible category, as the paper discusses the use of robots in carrying out natural language instructions. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible, as the paper discusses the use of sequence-to-sequence translation problems and other machine learning methods in interpreting navigation instructions.
